      <hedline>
        <hl1>Bush vs. Gore, Round 1: Now the People Debate; People or Bureaucrats</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Bloustein letter, commenting on October 4 editorial assessing debate between Vice Pres Al Gore and Gov George W Bush, says conceptual differences between candidates, especially regarding role of government, are stark and critically important and should be addressed by all voters</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The First Presidential Debate'' (editorial, Oct. 4):</p>
        <p>Conceptual differences between the two presidential contenders are stark and critically important. The main one -- are government bureaucrats more capable of running my life than I am? -- should be addressed by all voters.</p>
        <p>PAUL BLOUSTEIN  Cincinnati, Oct. 4, 2000</p>
      </block>
